<p>Can I use PHP socket for listening incoming data from port and save as a text file in webserver?<br> This is the sample code, I have found from PHP Sockets- how can I save the receive data in text file?</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;?php  $sock = socket_create_listen(0);  socket_getsockname($sock, $addr, $port);  print "Server Listening on $addr:$port\n";  $fp = fopen($port_file, 'w');  fwrite($fp, $port);  fclose($fp);  while($c = socket_accept($sock)) {     /* do something useful */     socket_getpeername($c, $raddr, $rport);     print "Received Connection from $raddr:$rport\n";  }  socket_close($sock);  ?&gt;   client.php:  &lt;?php  $fp = fopen($port_file, 'r');  $port = fgets($fp, 1024);  fclose($fp);  $sock = socket_create(AF_INET, SOCK_STREAM, SOL_TCP);  socket_connect($sock, '127.0.0.1', $port);  socket_close($sock);  ?&gt;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>